---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
const updated = '2026-04-18';
---
<Layout title="Terms & Conditions" description={`Terms governing your use of ${SITE.name}.`}>
  <article class="container-prose py-20 prose dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

    <p>
      These Terms govern your use of the {SITE.name} Android application (the "App") and this
      website (together, the "Service"). By installing or using the Service, you agree to these
      Terms. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>1. License</h2>
    <p>
      The App is free software, provided at no charge, and its source code is published under the
      GNU General Public License v3.0 on GitHub. You may use, modify, and redistribute it subject
      to the terms of that license. Nothing in these Terms overrides the rights granted by the
      underlying open-source license.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the Service in violation of any applicable law or regulation.</li>
      <li>Redistribute modified versions that falsely claim affiliation with {SITE.name}.</li>
      <li>Reverse engineer for the purpose of creating malicious derivatives.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided "as is" and "as available", without warranties of any kind, whether
      express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a
      particular purpose, or non-infringement. You use the Service at your own risk.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, {SITE.author} shall not be liable for any indirect,
      incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, including loss of data, loss of
      profits, or device malfunction, arising out of or in connection with your use of the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-party services</h2>
    <p>
      The Service itself does not integrate third-party services. However, the Service is
      distributed through Google Play, and your download and installation are additionally subject
      to Google's terms.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Changes to the Service</h2>
    <p>
      We may update, change, or discontinue the Service at any time without notice. We may also
      update these Terms; continued use after changes indicates acceptance.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with applicable law in the
      jurisdiction of the project maintainers, without regard to conflict-of-law principles.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these Terms? Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`}>{SITE.email}</a>.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
